# Project Coding Standards

## Code Style Guidelines
- Use consistent indentation (2 spaces for JS/TS, 4 spaces for Python)
- Follow naming conventions appropriate for {{.Language}}
- Write descriptive variable and function names
- Keep functions small and focused (< 20 lines when possible)

## Error Handling
- Always handle errors explicitly
- Use proper error types and messages
- Log errors with sufficient context
- Implement graceful degradation where appropriate

## Testing Requirements
- Write unit tests for all new functions
- Aim for >80% code coverage
- Include integration tests for critical paths
- Use descriptive test names that explain behavior

## Documentation Standards
- Document all public APIs
- Include usage examples in comments
- Keep README files up to date
- Document architectural decisions

## Git Workflow
- Use meaningful commit messages
- Create feature branches for new work
- Require code review before merging
- Keep commit history clean and logical

Remember: These standards apply to all code in this project. When suggesting changes, ensure they align with these guidelines.